@ParametersAreNonnullByDefault

Package it.polimi.ingsw.server.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Attack
    This interface schematizes an attack, which is the effect that a weapon has on one or more targets
    Coin
    This interface schematizes the currency used in the game, which is distinguished by its color
    Damageable
    This interface schematizes all entities that can receive damage
    Mover
    This interface is implemented by the attacks that can move the player itself or one of the targets
    TargetCalculator
    This interface schematizes all the possible ways to calculate which damageable entities are actual targets
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Ammo
    This class represents the ammos, which are the main currency of the game
    Block
    This class implements the generic block that constitutes the board
    Board
    This class implements the gameboard
    BonusTile
    This class represents the tiles that are picked during the game when a grab is executed on a turret block
    CompoundAction
    This class is used to offer to a player the list of all possible actions
    CompoundTargetCalculator
    This class uses other classes implementing TargetCalculator in order to cover more complex target position requirements
    DamageToken
    This class represents the tokens that is received upon being damaged or marked
    Deck<T>
    Class to manages cards of generic types T
    FixedDirectionTargetCalculator
    This class is a TargetCalculator that finds targets in a straight line from the starting point
    FixedDistanceTargetCalculator
    This class is a TargetCalculator that finds targets that is in a fixed range of moves away from the starting point
    FixedVisibilityTargetCalculator
    This class is a TargetCalculator that finds targets that are (or are not) visible from the starting point
    Match
    This class represents the match, which is the core of the model and contains all the information relative to the game status
    Player
    This class represents the player entity, storing all info about its status during the match
    PlayerInfo
    This class stores the information necessary to uniquely identify players
    PowerupTile
    This class represents the actual powerup tile, which can be in the Deck or owned by a Player
    Range
    This class represents a range of admissible int values
    SpawnpointBlock
    This class represents all blocks of the spawnpoint type, which allow a player to grab and put back weapons and also they are the starting blocks of the match
    TurretBlock
    This class represents all blocks of turret type, which are the blocks that refer to the bonus deck when a grab action occurs
    Weapon
    This class represents the most basic type of weapon of the game, which only has a basic attack
    WeaponWithAlternative
    This class inherits from the basic weapon and adds an alternative attack that can be used instead of the basic one
    WeaponWithMultipleEffects
    This class inherits from the basic weapon and it also offers powered attacks that can be used together with the basic attack
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    BasicAction
    Defines the set of basic actions
    BorderType
    This enum represents the possible types of border
    CoinColor
    This enum contains the possible coin colors
    Direction
    Define basic directions
    Match.Mode
    This enum contains the possible types of match
    PlayerColor
    This enum represents the colors of the player pawns
    PowerupType
    This enum differentiates the 4 possible powerup options
    TargetType
    This enum differentiates the possible type of targets of an attack
